    public static class FillLevelFunction.Builder<T>

    • Method Detail

      • add

        public FillLevelFunction.Builder<T> add(double upperBound,
                               T value)
        Adds a new element to the FillLevelFunction that we are creating. It will use the upperBound of the last element (or the lowerBound that we started with if it does not exist) as the lowerBound for the new element.
        Parameters:
        upperBound - The upperBound of the new element. This must always be larger than the lowerBound.
        value - The value that is to be associated with this element
        Returns:
        This FillLevelFunction.Builder

      • build

        public FillLevelFunction<T> build()
        Returns:
        A new immutable FillLevelFunction object that contains all the elements that have been added until now.
